    <h2>Most Important 10-Mark Questions — Units 6, 7 &amp; 8</h2>
    <button class="toggle-btn" style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.15);color:#7b3f00">▼</button>
  </div>
  <div class="tenmark-body">

    <div class="tenmark-unit-block">
      <div class="tenmark-unit-title text-u6">
        <span>🌡️</span> Unit 6 — Climate Change Questions
      </div>
      <ul class="tenmark-q-list">
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>Explain global warming — its causes and impacts on the environment and humans.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>What is climate change? Discuss its effects on forests, biodiversity and sea level.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>Explain Net Zero target and Carbon Sink with examples and diagrams.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>Write a detailed note on Climate Justice with examples.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>Why is limiting global warming to 1.5°C important? Explain with consequences of exceeding 2°C.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u6)">
          <span>Differentiate between Carbon Intensity and Energy Intensity with examples.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="tenmark-unit-block">
      <div class="tenmark-unit-title text-u7">
        <span>⚙️</span> Unit 7 — Environmental Management Questions
      </div>
      <ul class="tenmark-q-list">
        <li style="border-color:var(--u7)">
          <span>Explain Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) — its objectives, steps and importance.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u7)">
          <span>Discuss Circular Economy and the 3R concept with diagrams and examples.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u7)">
          <span>Explain ISO 14001 and Environmental Management System (EMS) with the PDCA cycle.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u7)">
          <span>Differentiate between Article 48A and Article 51A(g) with their significance.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u7)">
          <span>What is Life Cycle Analysis (LCA)? Explain its stages with an example.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="tenmark-unit-block">
      <div class="tenmark-unit-title text-u8">
        <span>📜</span> Unit 8 — Treaties &amp; Legislation Questions
      </div>
      <ul class="tenmark-q-list">
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Explain the Montreal Protocol — its objectives, actions and outcomes.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Compare the Kyoto Protocol (1997) and Paris Agreement (2015) — purpose, differences and significance.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Discuss the Ramsar Convention and CBD — objectives and importance for biodiversity.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Write short notes on COP, IPCC and IUCN — their roles and importance.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Explain the Environment Protection Act 1986 and Wildlife Protection Act 1972 with their objectives.</span>
        </li>
        <li style="border-color:var(--u8)">
          <span>Explain IUCN Red List categories with examples. What is the significance of these categories?</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Model Answer Box -->
    <div style="margin-top:20px">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px">
        <span>✍️</span> Sample Model Answers
      </h3>
      <div class="exam-q-box">
        <div class="eq-label">🎯 Sample 10-Mark Answer</div>
        <div class="eq-q">Q: Explain Net Zero and Carbon Sink.</div>
        <div class="eq-a">
          <strong>Carbon Sink:</strong> A carbon sink is anything that absorbs more CO₂ than it releases. Examples: Forests, Oceans, Wetlands, and Mangroves. They help reduce global warming by storing carbon naturally.<br><br>
          <strong>Net Zero:</strong> Net Zero is a state where the amount of greenhouse gases emitted equals the amount removed from the atmosphere. Formula: Carbon Emitted = Carbon Removed. Methods to achieve Net Zero include renewable energy, afforestation, and carbon capture technology. India's target is Net Zero by 2070.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="exam-q-box" style="margin-top:12px">
        <div class="eq-label">🎯 Sample 10-Mark Answer</div>
        <div class="eq-q">Q: Why is limiting global warming to 1.5°C important?</div>
        <div class="eq-a">
          Limiting warming to 1.5°C is important because: (1) It reduces the frequency and intensity of extreme weather events like floods, droughts, and heat waves. (2) It protects coastal areas from sea-level rise. (3) It preserves ecosystems and biodiversity from collapse. (4) It improves food and water security for billions of people. (5) It reduces the risk of irreversible climate tipping points. The Paris Agreement (2015) sets this target as the global goal.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

